docs.abstract: How should districts define political speech? Is a so-called thin blue line flag an example of political speech? What about a Black Lives Matter T-shirt?
docs.snippet: How should districts define political speech? Is a so-called thin blue line flag an example of political speech? What about a Black Lives Matter T-shirt?
docs.lead_paragraph: Many school districts have policies prohibiting employees from expressing political speech while carrying out their professional duties. For example, in such districts teachers can have a “Trump 2020” yard sign in front of their home, but they cannot wear a similar T-shirt to school. But sometimes determining what is, and what is not, political speech can be more tricky.

headline.main: Should Teachers Be Allowed to Wear Political Symbols?
